		<title type="html">Here a single DCI is transmitted (marked in red in the waterfall). It is FEC encoded in 4 CCEs, meaning that it uses 144 QPSK symbols. The size of the DCI before FEC is 43 bits (including the 16-bit CRC). It is addressed to the Paging RNTI. (3/4)</title>
